import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['count'] = pd.to_numeric(data['count'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='count', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['count'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['count'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of count?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance'] = pd.to_numeric(data['distance'], errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='distance', data=data, ax=ax, color='lightblue')
    ax.axvline(x=data['distance'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean: {data["distance"].mean():.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average distance between origin and destination?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='count', ascending=False).head(10)
    chart = sns.barplot(x='origin', y='count', hue='destination', data=data)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, horizontalalignment='right')
    plt.title('What are the top 10 most popular origin-destination pairs?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
